<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia daliensis" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Kuo in 
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al., 1985</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="synonym">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Synonym.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Melville, 1956" authorityName="Melville" authorityYear="1956" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudobythinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudobythinella" order="Mesogastropoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudobythinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979. Not Melville, 1956. Type species by original designation: 
<taxonomicName authority="Y.-Y.Liu &amp; W.-Z.Zhang, 1979" authorityName="Y. -Y. Liu &amp; W. -Z. Zhang" authorityYear="1979" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Pseudobythinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudobythinella jianouensis" order="Mesogastropoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jianouensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudobythinella jianouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shell ovoid to elongate ovoid or conical, smooth or with spiral microsculpture on the proto- and/or teleoconch. Apex conspicuously and more or less obliquely flattened. Aperture varying from ovoid-elliptical to circular; its palatal side curved and gradually passing into the basal side. Peristome continuous, attached at the parietal side or more or less protruding. Umbilicus minute or closed. Parietal part of the aperture smooth or with a lamella; columella smooth or with 2 spiral lamellae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Molecular data, which are available for only a limited number of the amnicolid species, are inconclusive regarding the status of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Akiyoshia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Akiyoshia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1954 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" genus="Akiyoshia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="class">Gastropoda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Truncatelloidea">Truncatelloidea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1863" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Amnicolidae</taxonomicName>
) (see also the more comprehensive phylogenetic reconstruction in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">Gittenberger et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). No DNA data are known for the type species of these nominal taxa, i.e., 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. daliensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Kuo, 1985 and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. uenoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="uenoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. uenoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1954. Furthermore, the species that are generally called 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Y. -Y. Liu &amp; W. -Z. Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1979" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia jianouensis" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jianouensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia jianouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1958" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Akiyoshia kobayashii" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kobayashii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Akiyoshia kobayashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1958 are sister species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 7. Maximum likelihood tree reconstructed with RAxML BlackBox (Stamatakis et al. 2008; GTR + G substitution model for each partition and 100 bootstrap replicates) based on the COI and 16 S rRNA dataset of Liu et al. (2014) and Guan et al. (2008), with new data in red. Numbers on branches denote bootstrap values&gt; 50." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641075" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7</figureCitation>
) that should be congeneric by definition. At present, their ranges in China and Japan, respectively, have been decisive for the generic classification. Pending additional data that can help solve this problem convincingly, we opted to still use the current, contradictory nomenclature (see also notes under 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. norbui" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="norbui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. norbui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially reported from a wide range in southern China, where it has been recorded with various species from the provinces of Yunnan, Sichuan, Guangxi, Hubei, Hunan, and Fujian (
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="391 - 427" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" refId="B3" refString="Davis, GM, Kang, ZB, 1995. Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 146: 391 - 427, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" title="Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" volume="146" year="1995">Davis and Kang 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B4" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="453 - 459" refId="B24" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Gong, X, Liu, H-X, 2000. Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene 62: 453 - 459, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" title="Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" volume="62" year="2000">Wilke et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Falniowski, A, Giusti, F, Bodon, M, Szarowska, M, 2001. Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1-21. https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" title="Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1 - 21." url="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" author="Liu, L" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B16" refString="Liu, L, Huo, G-N, He, H-B, Zhou, B, Attwood, SW, 2014. A phylogeny for the pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: e29. https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" title="A phylogeny for the pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: e 29." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" year="2014">Liu et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Regarding its occurrence in Japan, see foregoing notes. One species was described from northern India (
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B4" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
), three additional species were described from Nepal (
<bibRefCitation author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B21" refString="Nesemann, H, Sharma, S, Sharma, G, Khanal, SN, Pradhan, B, Shah, DN, Tachamo, RD, 2007. Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga river system (Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea, 57-102." title="Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga river system (Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea, 57 - 102." year="2007">Nesemann et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and, most recently, three species were described from Bhutan (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="21 - 28" refId="B7" refString="Gittenberger, E, Sherub, S, Stelbrink, B, 2017. Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan. ZooKeys 679: 21 - 28, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" title="Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" volume="679" year="2017">Gittenberger et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
). Here, we describe a fourth species from Bhutan and present, for the first time, a map of all known records of the genus (see Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of Erhaia species across Asia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641071" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
and Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Distribution of Erhaia species with coordinates (sorted from west to east) either provided by the source publication or estimated based on the locality information therein." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F5AE33FB49EC640676A0FD6F3C1BA1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="0F5AE33FB49EC640676A0FD6F3C1BA1D">1</tableCitation>
). As usual, it is unknown where snails may have been looked for in vain and thus our distribution maps (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of Erhaia species across Asia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641071" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution of Erhaia species described for Bhutan. Note that E. jannei and E. pelkiae were found to occur syntopically." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641074" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
) may represent human sampling activity rather than the real range of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Contrary to 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">Gittenberger et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, in the absence of DNA data, we refer to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. chandeshwariensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chandeshwariensis">
